## Component Specifications

### `src/types/` — Type Definitions
**Requirements**:
- [ ] All types explicitly defined (no `any`)
- [ ] Public types exported from `index.ts`

**Constraints**: No runtime dependencies, no circular imports

### `src/core/` — Core Logic
**Requirements**:
- [ ] Pure functions where possible
- [ ] Error handling via Result pattern
- [ ] Single responsibility per module

**Constraints**: No direct I/O, no framework-specific code

### `src/utils/` — Utilities
**Requirements**:
- [ ] Independently testable
- [ ] No side effects

**Constraints**: No business logic

### `test/` — Testing
**Requirements**:
- [ ] Unit coverage ≥ 80% for core/
- [ ] Integration tests for public APIs

**Conventions**: `<file>.test.ts`, descriptive test names

## Coding Standards

- Files: `kebab-case`, Classes: `PascalCase`, Functions: `camelCase`, Constants: `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE`
- Use `Result<T, E>` for expected failures, exceptions for programmer errors
- Keep functions under 30 lines, prefer composition over inheritance

